Linking textual statements with structured statements is a problem that affects several of the discussed methodologies, most notably peer-based inferences (see Section (ref), where existing statements need to be matched with statements on peers, and with textual evidence), and the KB-to-text relative recall assessment (Section (ref)). Due to their significant capabilities in latently representing and matching assertions in different formulations and representations, we may expect advances on these parts soon.